. As you can see in the screenshot above there\'s some minor promo for Linkdex underneath the box, which is an awesome service, and if you sign up for <a rel="nofollow" href="http://yoa.st/linkdex">Linkdex</a> using one of those links, or the ones in this post for that matter, I get a little bit of money.</p>\n<p>This release also features a set of updates to the General tab of the WordPress SEO box. The snippet preview has some enhancements, mostly relating to properly using ellipsis when the content is too long, as well as several JavaScript improvements. The focus keyword box, moved up in the previous release because it is so important for all these content SEO analyses, has gotten a new Google Suggest implementation using jQuery and jQuery UI that is far more robust than the previous one. Check it out:</p>\n<div><a rel="linkdex" href="http://cdn.yoast.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/snippet-preview.jpg"><img src="http://cdn.yoast.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/04/snippet-preview-300x223.jpg" alt="Snippet Preview with updated Focus Keyword Suggest" title="Snippet Preview with updated Focus Keyword Suggest" width="300" height="223" class="size-medium wp-image-4122" /></a><p>Snippet Preview with updated Focus Keyword Suggest</p></div>\n<p>Lastly, there are some new features in the indexing area, for instance allowing you to noindex, follow all paginated pages in taxonomies, so you can have /cat/seo/ indexed, but /cat/seo/page/2/ noindex, followed. In all, I think this is a killer update. There\'s one thing left to tackle, the way XML sitemaps are built. It works but I\'m not happy with it, once I\'ve finished that the plugin will come out of beta. For now, enjoy version 0.3, and let me know in the comments what you think! Bonus points for the person who guesses the focus keyword of this article :)</p>\n<p>So, <a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress/seo/">go grab the plugin</a>!</p>\n<p><a href="http://yoast.com/content-seo-wordpress-linkdex/">Content SEO made easier by WordPress, Yoast and Linkdex</a> is a post from <a href="http://yoast.com/about-me/">Joost de Valk</a>&#39;s <a href="http://yoast.com">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/">WordPress hosting</a>!</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/joostdevalk/~4/0Kf4dGcQgNA" height="1" width="1"/>";}i:8;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:39:"Site Speed tracking in Google Analytics";s:4:"link";s:58:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/tCnTM12XZqI/";s:4:"guid";s:24:"http://yoast.com/?p=4164";s:8:"comments";s:149:"http://yoast.com/site-speed-tracking-in-google-analytics/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=site-speed-tracking-in-google-analytics#comments";s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:145:"http://yoast.com/site-speed-tracking-in-google-analytics/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=site-speed-tracking-in-google-analyticsfeed/";}s:5:"slash";a:1:{s:8:"comments";s:2:"21";}s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 09 May 2011 13:38:25 +0100";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:13:"Joost de Valk";}s:8:"category";s:61:"AnalyticsWordPressGoogle AnalyticsSite SpeedWordPress Plugins";s:11:"description";s:785:"<p>Just a quickie: I just updated my Google Analytics for WordPress plugin to incorporate the new Site Speed tracking feature that Google announced last week. The feature is on by default and can be disabled in the advanced section of the settings. As you can see from the announcement post, this new feature helps you [...]</p><p><a href="http://yoast.com/site-speed-tracking-in-google-analytics/">Site Speed tracking in Google Analytics</a> is a post from <a href="http://yoast.com/about-me/">Joost de Valk</a>&#39;s <a href="http://yoast.com">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>";s:7:"content";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";s:2005:"<p><a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress/google-analytics/"><img src="http://cdn.yoast.com/wp-content/uploads/2007/09/GAfW-565-161-300x74.png" alt="Google Analytics for WordPress" title="Google Analytics for WordPress" width="300" height="74" class="alignright size-medium wp-image-2966" /></a>Just a quickie: I just updated my <a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress/google-analytics/">Google Analytics for WordPress</a> plugin to incorporate the new Site Speed tracking feature that <a href="http://analytics.blogspot.com/2011/05/measure-page-load-time-with-site-speed.html">Google announced</a> last week. The feature is on by default and can be disabled in the advanced section of the settings.</p>\n<p>As you can see from the announcement post, this new feature helps you determine questions like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Which landing pages are slowest?</li>\n<li>How does page load time vary across geographies?</li>\n<li>Does your site load faster or slower for different browsers?</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img alt="Site Speed report in Google Analytics" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-RoXO31TXnJE/TcCHhjJbQuI/AAAAAAAABNk/So-Ra5CM6Dc/s400/galt_blog.png" title="Site Speed report in Google Analytics" class="aligncenter" width="400" height="246" /></p>\n<p>You\'ll be able to find the results from this tracking under Content &rarr; Site Speed in Google Analytics. This release also fixes the slight error with the custom code option, that\'s now properly stripped from slashes.</p>\n<p><a href="http://yoast.com/site-speed-tracking-in-google-analytics/">Site Speed tracking in Google Analytics</a> is a post from <a href="http://yoast.com/about-me/">Joost de Valk</a>&#39;s <a href="http://yoast.com">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/">WordPress hosting</a>!</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/joostdevalk/~4/tCnTM12XZqI" height="1" width="1"/>";}s:10:"feedburner";a:1:{s:8:"origlink";s:140:"http://yoast.com/site-speed-tracking-in-google-analytics/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=site-speed-tracking-in-google-analytics";}s:7:"summary";s:785:"<p>Just a quickie: I just updated my Google Analytics for WordPress plugin to incorporate the new Site Speed tracking feature that Google announced last week. The feature is on by default and can be disabled in the advanced section of the settings. As you can see from the announcement post, this new feature helps you [...]</p><p><a href="http://yoast.com/site-speed-tracking-in-google-analytics/">Site Speed tracking in Google Analytics</a> is a post from <a href="http://yoast.com/about-me/">Joost de Valk</a>&#39;s <a href="http://yoast.com">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/">WordPress hosting</a>!</p>";s:12:"atom_content";s:2005:"<p><a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress/google-analytics/"><img src="http://cdn.yoast.com/wp-content/uploads/2007/09/GAfW-565-161-300x74.png" alt="Google Analytics for WordPress" title="Google Analytics for WordPress" width="300" height="74" class="alignright size-medium wp-image-2966" /></a>Just a quickie: I just updated my <a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress/google-analytics/">Google Analytics for WordPress</a> plugin to incorporate the new Site Speed tracking feature that <a href="http://analytics.blogspot.com/2011/05/measure-page-load-time-with-site-speed.html">Google announced</a> last week. The feature is on by default and can be disabled in the advanced section of the settings.</p>\n<p>As you can see from the announcement post, this new feature helps you determine questions like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Which landing pages are slowest?</li>\n<li>How does page load time vary across geographies?</li>\n<li>Does your site load faster or slower for different browsers?</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img alt="Site Speed report in Google Analytics" src="http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-RoXO31TXnJE/TcCHhjJbQuI/AAAAAAAABNk/So-Ra5CM6Dc/s400/galt_blog.png" title="Site Speed report in Google Analytics" class="aligncenter" width="400" height="246" /></p>\n<p>You\'ll be able to find the results from this tracking under Content &rarr; Site Speed in Google Analytics. This release also fixes the slight error with the custom code option, that\'s now properly stripped from slashes.</p>\n<p><a href="http://yoast.com/site-speed-tracking-in-google-analytics/">Site Speed tracking in Google Analytics</a> is a post from <a href="http://yoast.com/about-me/">Joost de Valk</a>&#39;s <a href="http://yoast.com">Yoast - Tweaking Websites</a>. \n\nA good WordPress blog needs good hosting, you don\'t want your blog to be slow, or, even worse, down, do you? Check out my thoughts on <a href="http://yoast.com/wordpress-hosting/">WordPress hosting</a>!</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/joostdevalk/~4/tCnTM12XZqI" height="1" width="1"/>";}i:9;a:14:{s:5:"title";s:31:"Yoast – New & Improved images";s:4:"link";s:58:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/joostdevalk/~3/rRXCSlWZvRw/";s:4:"guid";s:24:"http://yoast.com/?p=4146";s:8:"comments";s:111:"http://yoast.com/yoast-improved-image/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=yoast-improved-image#comments";s:3:"wfw";a:1:{s:10:"commentrss";s:107:"http://yoast.com/yoast-improved-image/#utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=yoast-improved-imagefeed/";}s:5:"slash";a:1:{s:8:"comments";s:2:"58";}s:7:"pubdate";s:31:"Mon, 25 Apr 2011 21:36:47 +0100";s:2:"dc";a:1:{s:7:"creator";s:13:"Joost de Valk";}s:8:"category";s:14:"OfftopicAvatar";s:11:"description";s:734:"<p>I\'ve been known online by my avatar for quite a few years now, even having people in conferences come up to me and say they recognized me from it. T