ref="http://www.elegantthemes.com/affiliates/idevaffiliate.php?id=17720&#038;keyword=nimble&#038;custom=21114">Nimble</a> is a big, bold, and beautiful theme that doesn’t let its own image get in the way. With each design it strive to strike a balance between style and function. Nimble’s colors are toned down but still delicious and its style is bold but still leaves room to breath. Browsing Nimble on a 27″ Cinema Display is quite a treat, but so is browsing the theme on a small screen as well due to Nimble’s fully responsive design. I’m quite pleased with how it turned out! As with all of our themes this one comes with some great features, so let’s take a closer look.</p>\n<p><img src="http://www.elegantthemes.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/nimble_blogpost_full.jpg" alt="WordPress Theme: Nimble" /></p>\n<h2>Fully Responsive Design</h2>\n<p>The use of mobile devices is on the rise, and it is important for your website to be ready for those mobile visitors. Nimble comes fully responsive, meaning that the design will adapt to whatever screen size is being used to browse. You website will look stunning and will be a breeze to read on mobile phones and desktop computers alike.</p>\n<p><img src="http://www.elegantthemes.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/nimble_blogpost_iphone.jpg" alt="Nimble" /></p>\n<p>And let’s not forget about tablets! Nimble will also look great on your iPad or Android tablet in both portrait and landscape mode.</p>\n<p><img src="http://www.elegantthemes.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/nimble_blogpost_ipad.jpg" alt="Nimble" /></p>\n<p>5 Unique Colors To Choose From</p>\n<p>As with all of our themes, Nimble comes with some great color choices. If the delicous sorbet orange isn’t your style, then try out the Blue, Green, Red or Gray options. There’s certainly a flavor for everyone.</p>\n<p><img src="http://www.elegantthemes.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/nimble_blogpost_colors.jpg" alt="Nimble" /></p>\n<p><a href="http://www.elegantthemes.com/affiliates/idevaffiliate.php?id=17720&#038;keyword=nimble&#038;custom=21114">DEMO and Feature Info</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:47:"http://theme10.com/wordpress-theme-nimble/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:42:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:58:"TinyPNG: Compress PNG images while preserving transparency";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:27:"http://theme10.com/tinypng/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"http://theme10.com/tinypng/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sun, 07 Oct 2012 16:54:47 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Open Source";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"http://themes.wpjam.com/?p=103";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:350:"PNG is useful on the web because it\'s the only widely supported format that can store partially transparent images. The format uses compression, but the resulting files can still be large. <a href="http://tinypng.org/">TinyPNG</a> that only works with PNG files, shrinks them -nearly- without loss that an eye can see and by keeping the transparency.";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Denis";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1512:"<p>PNG is useful on the web because it&#8217;s the only widely supported format that can store partially transparent images. The format uses compression, but the resulting files can still be large. </p>\n<p><img src="http://pic.fairyfish.com/2012/tinypng.png" alt="TinyPNG" /></p>\n<p><a href="http://tinypng.org/">TinyPNG</a> that only works with PNG files, shrinks them -nearly- without loss that an eye can see and by keeping the transparency.</p>\n<p>TinyPNG uses smart lossy compression techniques to reduce the file size of your PNG files. By selectively decreasing the number of colours in the image, fewer bytes are required to store the data. The effect is nearly invisible but it makes a very large difference in file size!</p>\n<p>When you upload a PNG (Portable Network Graphics) file, similar colours in your image are combined. This technique is called “quantisation”. Because the number of colours is reduced, 24-bit PNG files can be converted to much smaller 8-bit indexed colour images. All unnecessary metadata is stripped too. The result: tiny 8-bit PNG files with 100% support for transparency. Have your cake and eat it too!</p>\n<p>It works by drag and drop uploading the images to be minimized to the web interface and auto-generates the compressed ones.</p>\n<p>Using TinyPNG, it is easily possible to get 50%+ smaller sized images as they are converted to 8-bit PNGs (rather than 24bit) by using smart techniques.</p>\n<p>TinyPNG：<a href="http://tinypng.org/">http://tinypng.org/</a></p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:32:"http://theme10.com/tinypng/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:45:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"CSS FliterLab: Explore CSS Filters And CSS Custom Filters";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:76:"http://theme10.com/css-fliterlab-explore-css-filters-and-css-custom-filters/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:85:"http://theme10.com/css-fliterlab-explore-css-filters-and-css-custom-filters/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 02 Oct 2012 05:52:52 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Open Source";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"CSS3";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s: